
[1]humorously

   HU'MOROUSLY, adv. With a wild or grotesque combination of ideas; in a
   manner to excite laughter or mirth; pleasantly; jocosely. Addison
   describes humorously the manual exercise of ladies' fans.

   1. Capriciously; whimsically; in conformity with one's humor.

   We resolve by halves, rashly and humorously.
